---
import CaseStudy from "@/layouts/case-study.astro"
import { getProject } from "@/data/projects"

const project = getProject("creative-printing-job-submission-portal")!
---

<CaseStudy
  project={project}
  title="Creative Printing Job Submission Portal"
  description="A draft case study about redesigning a print-shop submission path so customers could move from project type to the right job request with less friction."
>
  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    This page is a placeholder for a future case study about the Creative
    Printing job submission portal redesign. The current framing comes from my
    resume and old portfolio notes: responsive icon-grid navigation, clearer
    information hierarchy, and a simpler path from project selection to
    submission.
  </p>

  <h2>Problem</h2>
  <!-- TODO: Add the original submission flow, user pain points, and the business context from Creative Printing. -->
  <p>
    Customers needed a clearer way to identify the kind of print job they were
    submitting and reach the correct request path without reading through
    unrelated service content.
  </p>

  <h2>Role</h2>
  <p>
    Web and graphic designer at Creative Printing and Internet Services, working
    across information architecture, interface design, and front-end
    implementation.
  </p>

  <h2>Next Draft Pass</h2>
  <!-- TODO: Add screenshots, before/after structure, final route labels, and any real outcome or qualitative feedback. -->
  <p>
    The next pass should add screenshots, define the submission categories, and
    describe what changed in the user flow without inventing performance
    metrics.
  </p>
</CaseStudy>
